source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1950, 1960, 1979, 1991, 2009 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2023; (f) only total population for 1970 Census; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the 2000, 2006, 2014, 2018-2019 MICS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2006; (b) birth-histories data from the 2014, 2018-2019 MICS; (c) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1991 Census and 2006 MICS; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1970, 1979, 1991, 2009 censuses and 2000, 2006, 2010, 2018-2019 MICS; (e) indirect estimates obtained from stable population assumption; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1950 Census and 2006, 2010, 2014, 2018-2019 MICS. In addition, the (a) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 1981; (b) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1979 Census and 2000 MICS; (c) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1950 Census and 2000, 2006 MICS; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1950, 1960 censuses and 1958-2002 Education Stats; (e) indirect estimates obtained from stable population assumption; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 2000 MICS have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2014; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) The demographic impact of AIDS has been factored into the mortality estimates; (d) estimates using HIV/AIDS model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0) and adult mortality (45q15) with UNAIDS estimates of adult HIV prevalence, and ART coverage for children and adults. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 2009 Census; (b) siblings deaths from the 2006 MICS; (c) maternal orphanhood from the 2000, 2006, 2010, 2014, 2018-2019 MICS; (d) paternal orphanhood from the 2000, 2006, 2010, 2014, 2018-2019 MICS; (e) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 2014 MICS; (f) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (g) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) siblings deaths from the 2014 MICS; (b) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1960, 1979, 1991 censuses and 2000, 2006 MICS; (c) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1960, 1979, 1991 censuses and 2000, 2014 MICS; (d) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2009; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2010, 2014 MICS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 2000, 2006 MICS; (d) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2018-2019 MICS; (b) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1950 Census; (c) recent household deaths from the 2009 Census have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
